{"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This article describes the KeyboardKit styling engine."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"While native iOS keyboards provide very little ways of customizing the look and feel of the keyboard, KeyboardKit-based keyboards can be styled and customized to great extent."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit uses "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardStyle","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" types to style its views. For instance, a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardStyle\/InputCallout"},{"type":"text","text":" style can be used to style a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Callouts\/InputCallout","isActive":true},{"text":" view.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardKitPro","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" unlocks a powerful theme engine and a bunch of themes. More information about Pro features can be found at the end of this article."}]},{"anchor":"Terminology","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Terminology"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit uses different names for different ways to style keyboards."}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardStyle","isActive":true},{"text":" style is ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"static"}]},{"text":" and can be applied to certain views.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardStyleProvider"},{"text":" is a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"dynamic","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" style provider that provides context-based styles.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardTheme"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" (Pro) is a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"static","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" style provider that can define, reuse and share styles."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can mix and match these different concepts as you see fit.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Resources & Assets","anchor":"Resources--Assets","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit comes with colors and assets that can be used to create native-looking keyboards.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Image"}]},{"type":"text","text":" has a bunch of keyboard-specific images, e.g. "},{"code":".keyboardBackspace","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Color","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" has a bunch of keyboard-specific colors, e.g. ","type":"text"},{"code":".standardButtonBackground","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardAction"},{"type":"text","text":" and other types have standard images, texts and colors."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For instance, to get the standard button image and text for an action, you can do this:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let context = KeyboardContext()","let image = KeyboardAction.command.standardButtonImage(for: context) \/\/ Command icon","let text = KeyboardAction.space.standardButtonText(for: context)     \/\/ Localized \"space\""],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Have a look at "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Understanding-Colors"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Understanding-Images"},{"text":" for more information about colors and images.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Styling-namespace","text":"Styling namespace","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit has a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Styling","isActive":true},{"text":" namespace that contains styling-related types.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The namespace doesn’t contain protocols, open classes, or types that are meant to be exposed at the top-level."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Keyboard appearance","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Keyboard-appearance"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A keyboard appearance determines whether or not the keyboard will be light or dark. It’s not the same as a ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"color scheme","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", which means that a keyboard can be dark(er) while still in light mode.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit has a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/Styling\/KeyboardAppearanceViewModifier"},{"type":"text","text":" that can be used to apply a keyboard appearance to a view:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["TextField(\"Enter text\", text: $text)","    .keyboardAppearance(.dark)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that applying a dark appearances will make iOS tell the extension that the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"color scheme","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" is dark, while this may in fact not be true."}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Keyboard-styles","level":2,"text":"Keyboard styles"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardStyle"},{"type":"text","text":" namespace contains many keyboard styles, like "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardStyle\/Button","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardStyle\/Callout"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardStyle\/EmojiKeyboard","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All styles can be modified, including most standard values. For instance, here we apply a red background to the standard ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardStyle\/Callout"},{"type":"text","text":" style:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["var style = KeyboardStyle.Callout.standard","style.backgroundColor = .red","KeyboardStyle.Callout.standard = style"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Most styles have a ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":".standard"}]},{"text":" style that you can use as a template. The standard styles can also be overwritten with a custom style to change the global default style of that component.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Keyboard-style-providers","level":2,"text":"Keyboard style providers","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In KeyboardKit, a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardStyleProvider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" can return dynamic styles for different parts of the keyboard. Unlike static styles, style providers can vary styles depending on the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardContext"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardAction","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" etc.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Views like the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/SystemKeyboard"},{"type":"text","text":" use a style provider to get a button style for each keyboard button, based on the button action, current device, etc."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit registers a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/StandardKeyboardStyleProvider","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" instance with "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardInputViewController\/services","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" when a keyboard is loaded. You can modify or replace this provider at any time.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"text":"Keyboard button styles","type":"heading","anchor":"Keyboard-button-styles"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Most view that support styling let you pass in a style in their initializer. For instance, here we apply a custom autocomplete toolbar style that makes the item title font bold:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["var style = KeyboardStyle.AutocompleteToolbar.standard","style.item.titleFont = .body.weight(.bold)","","let bar = AutocompleteToolbar(","    suggestions: [],","    style: style",")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardStyle\/Button"},{"text":" is different from most other styles, since it can style any view to look like a keyboard button, using the ","type":"text"},{"code":".keyboardButtonStyle(...)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" view modifier.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardStyle\/Button","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" style also doesn’t have a "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":".standard","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" style, since the style of a keyboard button depends on so many factors, such as button type, device type, keyboard appearance, color scheme, etc."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"How-to-create-a-custom-style-provider","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"How to create a custom style provider"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can create a custom style provider by inheriting "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/StandardKeyboardStyleProvider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and customize the parts you want, or implement the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardStyleProvider","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol from scratch.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For instance, here’s a custom provider that inherits ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/StandardKeyboardStyleProvider","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and makes all input buttons red:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["class CustomKeyboardStyleProvider: StandardKeyboardStyleProvider {","    ","    override func buttonStyle(","        for action: KeyboardAction,","        isPressed: Bool","    ) -> KeyboardStyle.Button {","        let style = super.buttonStyle(for: action, isPressed: isPressed)","        if !action.isInputAction { return style }","        style.backgroundColor = .red","        return style","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To use this provider instead of the standard one, just set the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardInputViewController\/services","isActive":true},{"text":" provider to this custom provider:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["class KeyboardViewController: KeyboardInputViewController {","","    override func viewDidLoad() {","        keyboardStyleProvider = CustomKeyboardStyleProvider()","        super.viewDidLoad()","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This will make KeyboardKit use your custom implementation instead of the standard one.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"👑-Pro-features","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"👑 Pro features"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"overridingTitle":"KeyboardKit Pro","type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit Pro"}],"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardKitPro"},{"text":" unlocks a theme engine that makes it a lot easier to define styles for a keyboard.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Themes","text":"Themes","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardTheme"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used to define a bunch of styles, such as button and background styles. You can also use other themes as templates to create your own custom themes."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit comes with many pre-defined themes:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["KeyboardTheme.standard","KeyboardTheme.swifty","KeyboardTheme.minimal","KeyboardTheme.candyShop","KeyboardTheme.colorful","KeyboardTheme.neon","KeyboardTheme.tron"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All pre-defined themes come with style variations that allow you to tweak parts of a theme:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["KeyboardTheme.standard(.pink)","KeyboardTheme.swifty(.blue)","KeyboardTheme.minimal(.midnight)","KeyboardTheme.candyShop(.cottonCandy)","KeyboardTheme.colorful(.purple)","KeyboardTheme.neon(.night)","KeyboardTheme.tron(.sark)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also define a custom style variation directly in the theme initializer:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["KeyboardTheme.standard(","    .init(tint: .black)",")"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Style variations make it easy to play within the style of a theme, and only modify the parts that are meant to be changed by the theme.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Custom themes","anchor":"Custom-themes"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can create completely custom themes, like this one that changes the primary button color:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["extension KeyboardTheme {","","    static var myCustomTheme: KeyboardTheme {","        get throws {","            var theme = try? KeyboardTheme(","                primaryBackgroundColor: .green","            )","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also use another theme as a template and tweak any parts of it:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["extension KeyboardTheme {","","    static var anotherTheme: KeyboardTheme {","        get throws {","            var theme = try? KeyboardTheme.standard","            theme.buttonStyles[.primary]?.backgroundColor = .green","            return theme","        }","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can then access your theme with ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardTheme.myCustomTheme"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" or just ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":".myCustomTheme"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" when passing in the theme as a function parameter."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Theme-based styling","anchor":"Theme-based-styling"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once you have a theme that you want to use, you can use the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ThemeBasedKeyboardStyleProvider"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["override func viewWillSetupKeyboard() {","    super.viewWillSetupKeyboard()","","    \/\/ Setup KeyboardKit Pro with a license","    setupPro(withLicenseKey: \"...\") { license in","        keyboardStyleProvider = ThemeBasedKeyboardStyleProvider(","            theme: .cottonCandy,","            keyboardContext: keyboardContext","        )","    } view: { controller in","        \/\/ Return your keyboard view here","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will make any view that uses the style provider (like "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/SystemKeyboard"},{"text":") use this theme. You can change this theme at any time.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can inherit "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"ThemeBasedKeyboardStyleProvider","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" to customize this theme-based provider even further, which lets you mix the benefits of themes and styles in even more ways."}]},{"name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since the theme engine requires KeyboardKit Pro, you must register this provider "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"after","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" registering your KeyboardKit Pro license key.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"important","type":"aside"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Pre-defined-themes","text":"Pre-defined themes","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can access all pre-defined themes with ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardTheme.{ID}"}]},{"type":"text","text":", for instance "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit.standard"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit.minimal(.pink)"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a list of all pre-defined themes with some style variations:"}]},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Theme"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}],[{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"code":".standard","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"standard.jpg","type":"image"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"standard-blue.jpg"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"standard-pink.jpg","type":"image"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"standard-green.jpg"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineCo